`std::async` je malo divlji zbog svog defaultnog execution policya koji je `async|deffered` i ne garantira bas da ce se izvrsiti na posebnom threadu, GCC je prije samo defferao execution do poziva na `.get()`, ocigledno to kod tebe nije slucaj jer ti stvarno smanji execution time, ali specificirati mu launch policy -> `std::async(std::launch::async, &DecisionTree::buildTree, this, true_branch, meta);` generalno nije losa ideja

dodatno, s obzirom da tvoj main thread nista ne radi, nego ceka oba futurea da se vrate, vjerojatno ti ne trebaju zasebni threadovi za oba brancha

evo moj take:
```
auto DecisionTree::buildTree(const Data& rows, const MetaData& meta) {
    const auto split{ Calculations::find_best_split(rows,meta) };   
    const double gain{ std::get<0>(split) };
    const Question& question{ std::get<1>(split) };

    if (gain == 0.0) {
        return Node{ Leaf{ Calculations::classCounts(rows) } };
    }

    const auto partitions{ Calculations::partition(rows, question) };

    const Data& true_branch{ std::get<0>(partitions) };
    const Data& false_branch{ std::get<1>(partitions) };

    std::future<Node> future1{ std::async(std::launch::async, &DecisionTree::buildTree, this, true_branch, meta) };
    Node right_node = buildTree(this, false_branch, meta);
    Node left_node { future1.get() };

    return Node{ std::move(left_node), std::move(right_node), question };
}
```

